cast.text:
Not-so-hot take on growing accounts:
It isn't easy anywhere. If you want to grow faster, then make connections, write, and generally put in the effort in a sustained manner.

I have found that people are more receptive to new connections here on Farcaster than anywhere else, by far.

text: speaking anecdotally, I invite fewer of my friends to FC now than I did a year or two ago. Still unpacking the reasons / thoughts behind that but curious if others feel the same.

I've been a part of the art community for 2.5 years on X & now here for a few months, & I can tell you with certainty that artists on @farcaster are at a crossroads.

Best case 1: There's some foundational shift where the fc ecosystem elevates these "quality content" creators & they can have a meaningful existence here.

Best Case 2: They go explore Lens or maybe back to X (where despite the algo, they get some recognition for their art from their peers).

Worst case: They get disenchanted with web3 altogether because they've been scammed, rugged, ignored, reduced to a number & pretty much treated like second class citizens regardless of where they exist. I worry about this the most.

Irony 1: The art community is the most vibrant community any social community can have. We literally have generational talent hanging out amongst us & most of us are unaware.

Irony 2: Artists who are here are the most tech forward of the normie bunch we'd wanna onboard. Biggest assets for any social platform.

1/2 üßµ

cast.text: I‚Äôve been extremely active here for 6 months.  I don‚Äôt invite new people to Farcaster anymore.  I tried to onboard a lot of people at the beginning.  A core of users stayed but 90% of the artist community I helped onboard are no longer active.  It‚Äôs a graveyard of user profiles that I brought on.  A focus on how to get those users back on the platform seems like a better bet than trying to convince someone new that it makes sense for them.

text:
First-time contributors to Farcaster often try to propose new features. 

We appreciate the energy, but this never ends up working. First-time contributors usually lack the context to identify design flaws and the clout to get people to adopt it. 

If you're serious about contributing, start with simple things like fixing bugs, writing docs, upgrading packages or improving the dev ex. This will help you build the context you need to start writing features.
@adrienne has been pinging me about this! we have a bunch of stuff we're working on, but overall it's a good idea!

Octant x Purple Retroactive Public Goods Funding

10 ETH will be distributed this round to support the Farcaster public goods ecosystem!

Octant staked 100,000 ETH and is distributing staking rewards to people building public goods. Octant is developed by the Golem Foundation and funding is dispersed via community voting of $GLM stakers. Learn more at /octant 

Thanks to prop #52 PurpleDAO pre allocated 5 ETH to this round and Octant is match funding this round with another 5 ETH for a total round of 10 ETH.

Anyone with a Purple Token and allowlisted Octant voters on Farcaster are eligible for voting. You can vote by simply liking a cast. You can like as many casts as you see fit.

How to get funding

Starting on August 30 at 12PM UTC, you have 2 weeks to do the following:

1. You need to cast inside /purple and
2. You need to use #retropgf in your cast to qualify for this round.

Optional, but encouraged:
3. You can also submit other people by casting with the following structure:
- credit @other_user

Most people don‚Äôt know I used to be a Travel Ambassador for a credit card co. The role combined 3 of my biggest passions: Photography, traveling & working the cc points system. 

I wasn‚Äôt paid to travel, but b/c I was earning the majority of my flights, hotels, and transpo via reward points, they hired me to document my journeys around the world. 

I‚Äôve been to 49 countries, gravitating to outdoor adventures & nature. I‚Äôm a hiker, biker, skier, climber, and surfer.

/adventure is a home for adrenaline junkies & nature lovers.

I‚Äôve been bad about promoting it, but that ends today.

I‚Äôll be sharing pics + stories of places I‚Äôve been fortunate to visit. Hopefully others will post theirs too so I can add some new spots to my bucket list. 

Will also mix in travel tips + gear + cc hacks + other fun stuff.

I‚Äôll kick it off tomorrow, but for now, enjoy this pic of the most picturesque football pitch on the planet located in the Lofoten Islands. If you squint really hard maybe you can see us ;)
